params.description: IP address or range, defined using CIDR notation, of requests that this rule applies to. Examples: 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.0.0/16 or 2001:db8::/32 or 2001:0db8:0000:0042:0000:8a2e:0370:7334. IP range prefixes should be properly truncated.
